Professor Stan Sangweni. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - ANC veteran Professor Stan Sangweni has died.
The 88-year-old struggle veteran died on Tuesday morning. During apartheid, he spent 30 years in exile living in The Netherlands, eSwatini, Zambia, Kenya and Ethiopia. Sangweni is the former chairperson of the Public Service Commission. He also served as the acting director of the United Nations Economic Commission for Africa. The ANC has expressed condolences to the Sangweni family and described him as a dedicated cadre. @MYANC mourns the passing of Professor Stanislaus (Stan) Skumbuzo Mzilankatha Sangweni #RIPProfessorStan pic.twitter.com/RaJadZflOj